#: ../../../reference/contrib/securetransport.rst:2
msgid "macOS SecureTransport"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/contrib/securetransport.rst:4
msgid ""
"`SecureTranport <https://developer.apple.com/documentation/security/"
"secure_transport>`_ support for urllib3 via ctypes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/contrib/securetransport.rst:7
msgid ""
"This makes platform-native TLS available to urllib3 users on macOS without "
"the use of a compiler. This is an important feature because the Python "
"Package Index is moving to become a TLSv1.2-or-higher server, and the "
"default OpenSSL that ships with macOS is not capable of doing TLSv1.2. The "
"only way to resolve this is to give macOS users an alternative solution to "
"the problem, and that solution is to use SecureTransport."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/contrib/securetransport.rst:14
msgid ""
"We use ctypes here because this solution must not require a compiler. That's "
"because Pip is not allowed to require a compiler either."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/contrib/securetransport.rst:17
msgid ""
"This code is a bastardised version of the code found in Will Bond's "
"`oscrypto <https://github.com/wbond/oscrypto>`_ library. An enormous debt is "
"owed to him for blazing this trail for us. For that reason, this code should "
"be considered to be covered both by urllib3's license and by `oscrypto's "
"<https://github.com/wbond/oscrypto/blob/master/LICENSE>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/contrib/securetransport.rst:23
msgid "To use this module, simply import and inject it:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/contrib/securetransport.rst:25
msgid ""
"import urllib3.contrib.securetransport\n"
"urllib3.contrib.securetransport.inject_into_urllib3()"
msgstr ""
